# Problem
In order to deal with a higher variety of situations pertaining changes in the number of drones and sensors, we are going to try a strategy of using a sequential model (perhaps Transformer based). The idea is reading observations a a sequence of sensor and drone information. Sequences can have variable size; thus, our model will be able to perform no matter the number of drones and sensors.

# Solution
I've created a new type of network I'm calling an encoder, inspired by the transformer architecture. It's composed of many configurable heads that read flat or sequential data into an embedding form that gets mixed to generate the output. For now I'm testing with flat inputs only.

# Results
The implementation is working but performance plummeted. We need to run another hyper-parameter trial as the change in model might benefit from other parameters.